      • vector

        public static <T> ListBuilder<T,Vector<T>> vector(T... values)
        Creates a builder populating a new Vector. Note that if you just want a synchronized list, you can use the following: 
         
 ListBuilder.<Whatever>array()
              .in(Collections::synchronizedList)
              .add(whatever)
              .build()
        This is provided primarily for compatibility with legacy code.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Ye element type
        Parameters:
        values - Initial values
        Returns:
        Yon builder
        See Also:
        Collections.synchronizedList(java.util.List<T>)

      • in

        public <J extends List<T>> ListBuilder<T,J> in(Function<L,J> wrapper)
        Returns a new builder populating a list which is the result of applying the given function to the existing list.

        Usage: 

         
 ListBuilder.array(1, 2, 3).in(Collections::unmodifiableList)

        Note that this may change whether further mutations are supported.

        Type Parameters:
        J - The new list type
        Parameters:
        wrapper - The wrapping or transforming function
        Returns:
        A new builder
